## D&R Rule Management

```bash
# List all rules
limacharlie dr list --oid $LC_OID --output yaml

# Get a rule definition
limacharlie dr get --key "<rule-name>" --oid $LC_OID --output yaml

# Enable a disabled rule (after review)
limacharlie dr set --name "<rule-name>" --enabled true --oid $LC_OID

# Disable a rule
limacharlie dr set --name "<rule-name>" --enabled false --oid $LC_OID

# Validate before deploying
limacharlie dr validate --detect detect.yaml --respond respond.yaml --oid $LC_OID

# List FP rules
limacharlie dr fp list --oid $LC_OID --output yaml
```

> [!CAUTION]
> **Never write D&R rules or LCQL queries manually.** Always use the AI generation tools.

See [D&R Overview](https://docs.limacharlie.io/3-detection-response/) and [Detection Operators](https://docs.limacharlie.io/8-reference/detection-logic-operators/).

