## LCQL Queries

> [!CAUTION]
> **Never write LCQL queries manually.** LCQL uses org-specific pipe-separated syntax.

```bash
# Generate a query from natural language
limacharlie ai generate-query --prompt "show all NEW_PROCESS events in the last hour" \
  --oid $LC_OID --output yaml

# Validate before running (mandatory)
limacharlie search validate --query "<generated-query>" --oid $LC_OID --output yaml

# Run the query (calculate timestamps with bash first!)
START=$(date -d '1 hour ago' +%s)
END=$(date +%s)
limacharlie search run --query "<validated-query>" --start $START --end $END \
  --oid $LC_OID --output yaml
```

See [LCQL Documentation](https://docs.limacharlie.io/4-data-queries/).

